article.headline: Pennsylvania 66, Elon 64
article.story: ELON, N.C. (AP) -- Ibrahim Jaaber scored 14 points to lift Penn past Elon 66-64 on Saturday. Steve Danley had 11 points and eight rebounds for Penn (7-6), which scored 28 points off turnovers and led 33-32 at the half. Chris Chalko led three players in double-digit scoring with 17 points for Elon (3-10), which shot 71.4 percent from the free-throw line and got 17 points from the bench. Chalko made five of nine from 3-point range. LeVonn Jordan had 16 points and seven rebounds and Brett James had 15 points and eight rebounds for Elon.
